## Conventions
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use `async/await` over `.then()` chains
- Error messages should be user-facing and helpful
- All API responses follow `{ data, error }` shape

## Testing
- Run tests: `npm test`
- Tests must pass before any PR is opened
- Write tests for any new public function

## Things To Avoid
- Do NOT introduce new dependencies without checking if an existing one covers it
- Do NOT use `any` type in TypeScript
- Do NOT hardcode environment-specific values — use env vars
- Do NOT modify the database schema without explicit approval

